Echomail to SYSOP
By Ed Gavin
   1:267/161

I've been reading the FN_SYSOP & SYSOP areas lately without it
being flagged to my attention on a daily basis like some others
out there in Echoland. Never to be outdone by other nets, the
Fido Sysops have created yet another means of irritating
ourselves. The not-so-origional originator of our latest screen
sport of under skin crawling, Alan Boritz took the opportunity
to let a portion of Fido-world know that their BBS software
wasn't working as he intended.

Since messaging to SYSOP is not an entirely new phenom in
Echoland it is hard to blame/credit Alan for the sole creation
of the sport. But like Ruth to baseball Boritz has raised the
level of the sport out of the cornfields and into our very
lives. Unfortunately 1995 doesn't look promising for either.

Our very own Sultan of Swat deserves recognition for his record
before it just becomes another passing fad or just another
sinking feeling in the annals of net history. In order to
enshrine our heros we must recognize their contributions and
what better way than to name the sport after them. The
originators of junk mail never got the recognition  they
deserved, the first spammers are long forgotten, let us never
forget Alan's first posts to SYSOP.

By consensus we may decide an appropriate name we can recognize
the talents of our very own! I'd propose we all remember Alan
with a catchy nickname for his sport, something like, "Boritzing
the Sysop" or "Boritzing- Behavior" before the tradition fades
away with the "Boritz Bug-Fix"!

Boritzing my way through the inbound.

Ed

