WEIRDNEWS Conference Available

by David Brien
Sysop, 1:107/725

The WEIRDNEWS Conference contains strange but true facts, like:

   Mankind makes up 0.00000000000000000000013 percent of all
   the earth's living things.

and news items, such as:

   In Kalama, Washington, 83 year old E.C. Boone hit a dog with his
   pickup truck. He stopped, and his 86 year old wife, May Belle, got
   out to see how badly the animal was hurt. According to Police Chief
   Ron Pease, the husband "Looked out the mirror and thought she was
   motioning for him to back up and started to back up. In the meantime,
   she walked behind the truck and he backed over her. She started to
   hollar and scream, then he put the truck in forward and drove over
   her again."

culled from magazines and newswires around the globe by an occasional
author of such collections, Jon Standish. Jon is currently posting
about 20 message a week, each about 2K. This is not a read-only
conference, but it reads like one. Of course, everyone is encouraged
to post responses and new items.

If you think your callers would enjoy reading WEIRDNEWS, why not pick
it up? The conference is available to all by sending a netmail to
SYSOP@1:107/725.

